This paper deals with the problem of impartial selection in elections, which is a topic in computational social choice (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the optimality of different mechanisms, which is a common theme in algorithmic game theory (cs.AI). The results are based on mathematical analysis and proofs, which suggests that the paper could also be relevant to the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the performance of different mechanisms in terms of their guarantees, which is a topic in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of designing near-optimal mechanisms, which is a topic in computational economics (cs.EC).
